        <argsstring>(string fileName)</argsstring>
        <name>LoadInstance</name>
        <qualifiedname>Assets.Scripts.Scheduling.Unity.TaillardValidator.LoadInstance</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>string</type>
          <declname>fileName</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Loads and deserializes a Taillard JSON instance from the <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity" kindref="compound">Unity</ref> Resources system. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Resolves the asset at <computeroutput>Resources/Instances/</computeroutput> &lt;fileName&gt; using <computeroutput>Resources.Load&lt;TextAsset&gt;</computeroutput>. If the asset is not found, logs a descriptive error including the expected file path and returns <computeroutput>null</computeroutput>. If the asset is found but JSON parsing fails, logs the exception message and returns <computeroutput>null</computeroutput>. Uses <computeroutput>Newtonsoft.Json.JsonConvert</computeroutput> rather than <computeroutput>JsonUtility</computeroutput> to support jagged array deserialization required by TaillardInstance.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fileName</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Filename without extension, e.g. <computeroutput>&quot;ta01&quot;</computeroutput>. Must match a <computeroutput>TextAsset</computeroutput> located at <computeroutput>Assets/Resources/Instances/</computeroutput> &lt;fileName&gt;.json.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The deserialized TaillardInstance on success, or <computeroutput>null</computeroutput> if the file is missing or the JSON cannot be parsed. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
