    <sectiondef kind="public-func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity_1_1_taillard_validator_1af1f835538ee83158a1a47e6c5c695030" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void Assets.Scripts.Scheduling.Unity.TaillardValidator.LoadAndValidate</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>LoadAndValidate</name>
        <qualifiedname>Assets.Scripts.Scheduling.Unity.TaillardValidator.LoadAndValidate</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Loads the configured Taillard instance and runs the full validation pipeline. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Executes four sequential steps:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Load the JSON instance from <computeroutput>Resources/Instances/</computeroutput> via LoadInstance. Aborts early if the file is missing or cannot be parsed.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Validate scheduling constraints (precedence, no machine overlap, bound checks) using ValidationRunner.ValidateConstraints with DispatchingRule.SPT_SMPT. All violations are logged as errors via <computeroutput>Debug.LogError</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Run dispatching rules: all rules via ValidationRunner.RunAllRules if <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity_1_1_taillard_validator_1a6af62e9c4c5baa1620e068ae69338cd1" kindref="member">runAllRules</ref> is <computeroutput>true</computeroutput>, otherwise a single rule via ValidationRunner.RunSingle. Results are colour-coded green / yellow / red based on gap percentage.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Optionally print a Gantt schedule to the console if <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity_1_1_taillard_validator_1aa4fd787eabc293a0c6abe41296aaf692" kindref="member">printSchedule</ref> is <computeroutput>true</computeroutput>, using a fresh DESSimulator run with <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity_1_1_taillard_validator_1a9c74720d5f136866a9649fb906071a8f" kindref="member">singleRule</ref>.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Also callable from the <ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity" kindref="compound">Unity</ref> Inspector via the <computeroutput>&quot;Run Validation&quot;</computeroutput> context menu without entering Play Mode. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="C:/Users/Mike/Documents/GitHub/Capstone/Capstone/Assets/Scripts/Scheduling/Unity/TaillardValidator.cs" line="73" column="21" bodyfile="C:/Users/Mike/Documents/GitHub/Capstone/Capstone/Assets/Scripts/Scheduling/Unity/TaillardValidator.cs" bodystart="73" bodyend="120"/>
      </memberdef>
    </sectiondef>
    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="namespace_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity" kindref="compound">Unity</ref> entry point for loading and validating Taillard JSP benchmark instances. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Attach to any GameObject in the scene. On Start, or manually via the <computeroutput>&quot;Run Validation&quot;</computeroutput> context menu entry, the component loads a TaillardInstance from <computeroutput>Resources/Instances/</computeroutput>, runs constraint checks through ValidationRunner, executes one or all DispatchingRule variants, and optionally prints a Gantt schedule to the console via DESSimulator.PrintSchedule.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>JSON files must be placed at <computeroutput>Assets/Resources/Instances/</computeroutput> &lt;name&gt;.json and referenced by filename without the <computeroutput></computeroutput>.json extension via <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_unity_1_1_taillard_validator_1a2503225f19ffc3f2e69f142c657e366a" kindref="member">instanceFileName</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
